{"source": "docs", "batch_index": 155, "chunks": [{"chunk_id": "daf55e3cbfb7", "text": "### 5.3 The For-In Loop (Iterating)\n\nLoop through items in a collection:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.3 The For-In Loop (Iterating)", "chunk_id": "daf55e3cbfb7"}}, {"chunk_id": "9f0192eccd5f", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.3 The For-In Loop (Iterating)", "chunk_id": "9f0192eccd5f"}}, {"chunk_id": "0b8c8243f321", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # We'll learn about lists soon!\n    fruits = [\"apple\", \"banana\", \"cherry\"];\n\n    for fruit in fruits {\n        print(f\"I like {fruit}\");\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.3 The For-In Loop (Iterating)", "chunk_id": "0b8c8243f321"}}, {"chunk_id": "1777fd5deffe", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.3 The For-In Loop (Iterating)", "chunk_id": "1777fd5deffe"}}, {"chunk_id": "d714665e7f59", "text": "### 5.4 Breaking Out of Loops\n\nSometimes you want to stop a loop early:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.4 Breaking Out of Loops", "chunk_id": "d714665e7f59"}}, {"chunk_id": "030d94d7201e", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.4 Breaking Out of Loops", "chunk_id": "030d94d7201e"}}, {"chunk_id": "714534f4f917", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Find first number divisible by 7\n    for i = 1 while i <= 100 with i += 1 {\n        if i % 7 == 0 {\n            print(f\"Found it: {i}\");\n            break;  # Exit the loop immediately\n        }\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.4 Breaking Out of Loops", "chunk_id": "714534f4f917"}}, {"chunk_id": "7acdcacb71ee", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.4 Breaking Out of Loops", "chunk_id": "7acdcacb71ee"}}, {"chunk_id": "2eaf30d9b44b", "text": "### 5.5 Skipping Iterations\n\nSkip to the next iteration without running the rest of the loop body:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.5 Skipping Iterations", "chunk_id": "2eaf30d9b44b"}}, {"chunk_id": "7d279369b74d", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.5 Skipping Iterations", "chunk_id": "7d279369b74d"}}, {"chunk_id": "1fa386f0d512", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    # Print only odd numbers\n    for i = 1 while i <= 10 with i += 1 {\n        if i % 2 == 0 {\n            continue;  # Skip even numbers\n        }\n        print(i);\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.5 Skipping Iterations", "chunk_id": "1fa386f0d512"}}, {"chunk_id": "16d3b849d89f", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.5 Skipping Iterations", "chunk_id": "16d3b849d89f"}}, {"chunk_id": "a7a341dbfae0", "text": "### 5.6 Practice Exercises\n\n**Challenge 1:** Write a loop that prints all multiples of 3 from 3 to 30.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "a7a341dbfae0"}}, {"chunk_id": "7d6bcb1df5be", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "7d6bcb1df5be"}}, {"chunk_id": "77b38599b4b6", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    for i = 3 while i <= 30 with i += 3 {\n        print(i);\n    }\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "77b38599b4b6"}}, {"chunk_id": "8daa915e2b31", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "8daa915e2b31"}}, {"chunk_id": "868cb1296daa", "text": "**Challenge 2:** Write a countdown from 10 to 1, then print \"Blast off!\"", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "868cb1296daa"}}, {"chunk_id": "7d6bcb1df5be", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "7d6bcb1df5be"}}, {"chunk_id": "7251c8c9e6b5", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    count = 10;\n    while count > 0 {\n        print(count);\n        count -= 1;\n    }\n    print(\"Blast off!\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "7251c8c9e6b5"}}, {"chunk_id": "8daa915e2b31", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "8daa915e2b31"}}, {"chunk_id": "29139b0ef784", "text": "---", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "5.6 Practice Exercises", "chunk_id": "29139b0ef784"}}, {"chunk_id": "28b900f95ea5", "text": "## 6. Organizing Code: Functions\n\nFunctions are reusable blocks of code that do specific tasks. Think of them as mini-programs within your program.", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6. Organizing Code: Functions", "chunk_id": "28b900f95ea5"}}, {"chunk_id": "cfe3ad9a05a5", "text": "### 6.1 Creating Your First Function\n\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.1 Creating Your First Function", "chunk_id": "cfe3ad9a05a5"}}, {"chunk_id": "14dd702da8fb", "text": "```jac\n# Define the function\ndef greet {\n    print(\"Hello, there!\");\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    # Use (call) the function\n    greet();\n    greet();\n    greet();\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.1 Creating Your First Function", "chunk_id": "14dd702da8fb"}}, {"chunk_id": "dde4297fb60d", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.1 Creating Your First Function", "chunk_id": "dde4297fb60d"}}, {"chunk_id": "2b9beb546b8e", "text": "### 6.2 Functions with Parameters\n\nMake functions more flexible by giving them inputs:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "2b9beb546b8e"}}, {"chunk_id": "7adf5d4aee13", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "7adf5d4aee13"}}, {"chunk_id": "186b3d941065", "text": "```jac\ndef greet(name: str) {\n    print(f\"Hello, {name}!\");\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    greet(\"Alice\");\n    greet(\"Bob\");\n    greet(\"Charlie\");\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "186b3d941065"}}, {"chunk_id": "d3810c4c0c66", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "d3810c4c0c66"}}, {"chunk_id": "5ffc4f95f1cc", "text": "**Breaking it down:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "5ffc4f95f1cc"}}, {"chunk_id": "3662dd65b86c", "text": "- `name: str` - This is a **parameter** (input)\n- `: str` - Type annotation (optional but recommended)\n- When you call `greet(\"Alice\")`, `\"Alice\"` becomes the value of `name`", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.2 Functions with Parameters", "chunk_id": "3662dd65b86c"}}, {"chunk_id": "ee0c6ade7ce1", "text": "### 6.3 Multiple Parameters\n\nFunctions can take multiple inputs:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.3 Multiple Parameters", "chunk_id": "ee0c6ade7ce1"}}, {"chunk_id": "f242e38951d9", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.3 Multiple Parameters", "chunk_id": "f242e38951d9"}}, {"chunk_id": "6d4b67cf3bbc", "text": "```jac\ndef add(x: int, y: int) {\n    sum = x + y;\n    print(f\"{x} + {y} = {sum}\");\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    add(5, 3);\n    add(10, 20);\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.3 Multiple Parameters", "chunk_id": "6d4b67cf3bbc"}}, {"chunk_id": "7617cf17fcdb", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.3 Multiple Parameters", "chunk_id": "7617cf17fcdb"}}, {"chunk_id": "2dbc23a95d2b", "text": "### 6.4 Returning Values\n\nInstead of just printing, functions can send values back:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "2dbc23a95d2b"}}, {"chunk_id": "f03d2b2eaaec", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "f03d2b2eaaec"}}, {"chunk_id": "a06d89673c3b", "text": "```jac\ndef add(x: int, y: int) -> int {\n    return x + y;\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    result = add(5, 3);\n    print(result);  # Shows: 8\n\n    # Use directly in calculations\n    total = add(10, 20) + add(5, 5);\n    print(total);  # Shows: 40\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "a06d89673c3b"}}, {"chunk_id": "1b49896ddcec", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "1b49896ddcec"}}, {"chunk_id": "6543ddd9a4b4", "text": "**Breaking it down:**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "6543ddd9a4b4"}}, {"chunk_id": "3224ac4b736e", "text": "- `-> int` - This function returns an integer\n- `return x + y;` - Send this value back to whoever called the function\n- The returned value can be stored in a variable or used directly", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.4 Returning Values", "chunk_id": "3224ac4b736e"}}, {"chunk_id": "9246512b8580", "text": "### 6.5 Default Parameters\n\nGive parameters default values:", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.5 Default Parameters", "chunk_id": "9246512b8580"}}, {"chunk_id": "78ef47511723", "text": "<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.5 Default Parameters", "chunk_id": "78ef47511723"}}, {"chunk_id": "b865e7f22fcf", "text": "```jac\ndef greet(name: str = \"friend\", excited: bool = False) {\n    if excited {\n        print(f\"HELLO, {name}!!!\");\n    } else {\n        print(f\"Hello, {name}.\");\n    }\n}\n\nwith entry {\n    greet();                          # Uses defaults\n    greet(\"Alice\");                   # Uses name, default excited\n    greet(\"Bob\", True);               # Both specified\n    greet(excited=True, name=\"Eve\");  # Named parameters\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.5 Default Parameters", "chunk_id": "b865e7f22fcf"}}, {"chunk_id": "67306e80b4f9", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.5 Default Parameters", "chunk_id": "67306e80b4f9"}}, {"chunk_id": "cbbb146638fa", "text": "### 6.6 Why Use Functions?\n\n**1. Avoid Repetition**", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.6 Why Use Functions?", "chunk_id": "cbbb146638fa"}}, {"chunk_id": "1321fb103a89", "text": "Bad:\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.6 Why Use Functions?", "chunk_id": "1321fb103a89"}}, {"chunk_id": "9cc791bd03c0", "text": "```jac\nwith entry {\n    print(\"Welcome!\");\n    print(\"Please enter your name.\");\n    # ... 20 more lines ...\n\n    # Later in code...\n    print(\"Welcome!\");\n    print(\"Please enter your name.\");\n    # ... same 20 lines again ...\n}\n```", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.6 Why Use Functions?", "chunk_id": "9cc791bd03c0"}}, {"chunk_id": "77308a96778c", "text": "</div>", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.6 Why Use Functions?", "chunk_id": "77308a96778c"}}, {"chunk_id": "248918cff4f2", "text": "Good:\n<div class=\"code-block\">", "meta": {"source": "jaseci_docs", "type": "official_doc", "upsample_weight": 3, "file": "tutorials/language/coding_primer.md", "section": "6.6 Why Use Functions?", "chunk_id": "248918cff4f2"}}], "near_dup_candidates": []}